8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.25a35197-5be1-40a6-bf32-1afdddc2bf66.description=
Snopsis\: Scriptlet that grabs all keys and out puts only keys that have Local values.  This is to emulate an ARGV type functionality.  Will only provide inputs of direct flow calling this operation.

Inputs\: None

Results\:
All local variables in argv format\: "index1\=value1 index2\=value2a+value2b index3\=value3a,value3b,value3c..."
Internal variables that can be potentially disregaurded\: (example was runCLU)
username
execution_thread_id
RS_Previous_Transition
webserviceHost
errorDetails
Result
RS_Previous_Response
password
flowUuid
webservicePort

Responses\:
failure - Something went wrong
success - Built argv list

8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.3688931e-70f2-45dc-830c-179b1dfd329a.description=
Runs an SSH command

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address
command - the command to execute
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty (may mangle stdout and stderr if set to true)
username - username to connect as
password - password
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete

Responses\:
success - the command was executed successfully
failure - the command could not be executed

Extra Results\:
STDERR - the STDERR of the command
STDOUT - the STDOUT of the command

8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.80bd9477-9a67-45c0-a527-6013051ecc14.description=
Executes a command from the command line of a remote RAS.

On unix we cannot mandate what type of shell to be used (sh, bash, ksh, csh, etc), so be sure to include the shell in your command
if you need things like file redirection.  Example\:
sh -c "ls -lha /etc > /tmp/myfile"

On Windows, this command will prepend cmd.exe /C or command.exe /C to the command you specify, so there is no need to pass that into this operation.

Inputs\:
    command - the command to execute.
    arguments - any arguments to command.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command.
    path - The path to the commands executable
    cmd_timeout - Timeout in milliseconds before the command is considered failed when returnImmediately is false.
Default value\: 100000 (100 seconds).
    returnImmediately - If true, the operation will execute the command and return immediately.  It will not wait for the command to finish.
Valid values\: true, false.
Default value\: false.

Responses\:
    success - The command executed successfully.
    failure - The command failed to execute.

Results\:
    STDOUT - The standard output of the command.
    STDERR - The standard error output of the command.
8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.c45b026b-3ab0-4078-b787-2cb4e06e709c.callout=CLU internal global\: caller\=HPOO 8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO, running on HPNA.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script libraries on $override_JRAS is running here\:  /data01/hosteng/Common_Library.tcl

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Javascript operator converts local HPOO variables into "index1\=value1 index2\=value2..." format
3) Operator runs command\:/usr/bin/execpt against local RAS script on $override_JRAS

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.
router		- Device target IP or DNS

Results\:
 flowOutput - Raw data back from ssh/telnet to $router commands

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${router}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${router}
8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.e33db047-f864-452d-8e7e-1b37271d999a.description=
Operation to check for null or empty string local variables.

Inputs\:

inputList\:  comma seperated list of variables to check

Reponsses\:
hasNull\:  at least one variable is null or has an empy string for a value
noNulls\:  all variables have a value

Result\:  List of variables that are null or empty strings
8bf4f837-38e6-48cb-85e1-eecdea138b29.e8d0a867-8ec0-4ffd-b502-8f0bcbb619f0.description=
Replaces a substring within a string.

Inputs\:
input - The input string
replace - The text to replace
replaceWith - The text to replace with

Responses\:
success - succeeded in updating string.
failure - was unable to replace for some reason

Returns\:
The string after the replace.
